## Reproducible playbook

1. Clone the repo, `cd` in.
2. Set up the language toolchain pinned in the repo (`.python-version`, `go.mod`, `rust-toolchain.toml`).
3. Install dev deps: `pip install -e .[dev]` / `go mod download` / `cargo build`.
4. Run unit tests.
5. Run integration / golden-output tests.
6. Smoke-test the binary against a real input fixture in `tests/fixtures/`.
7. Build a release artefact and re-run smoke tests against the built binary, not the source — they catch different bugs.
8. Bump version, tag, push, let the release pipeline publish.

